Information about the datasets 

========
Datasets
========

Chronicle Data Set 1 (Chr-1)	
Chronicle Data Set 2 (Chr-2)	
Historical Source Data Set (source-hist)	
Contemporary Source Data Set (source-cont)	
Author Data Set (author-intros)	

===============================
Chronicle Data Set 1 (Chr-1)
===============================

Text fragments from the first section of the chronicle which focuses on the history of Purmerend and the surrounding area. Fragments of text which are found between inverted commas in the original manuscript are referred to as 'copy' fragments and fragments of text which are outside of inverted commas in the original manuscript are referred to as 'no-copy' fragments. The copied fragments are mostly copied from 17th and 18th century history books.

Scans of the chronicle can be found at the website of the Noord-Hollands archief in Haarlem: https://noord-hollandsarchief.nl/bronnen/archieven?mivast=236&mizig=210&miadt=236&micode=143&milang=nl&mizk_alle=louwen&miview=inv2

This section of the chronicle consists of the first two volumes:
Albert Pietersz. Louwen, Kronijk Der Stad Purmerende Bevattende Der Selver Opkomste En Voortgang, Manuscript, Part 1 (Purmerend, 1766), Noord Hollands Archief Haarlem, 143 Collectie van Louwen, A. Pietersz., inv. nr. 18. (495 pages). 
And 
Part 2, Volume 1 (Purmerend, 1774), Noord Hollands Archief Haarlem, 143 Collectie van Louwen, A. Pietersz., inv. nr. 19. (288 pages)
N.B. Part 2 volume 1 of the chronicle is of a hybrid character: part of it describes contemporary events, notably the visit of Christan the Seventh, King of Danmark to Purmerend, but a large part is dedicated to the history of a mermaid that presumably was caught in the waters near Purmerend in the fifteenth century.

===============================
Chronicle Data Set 2 (Chr-2)
===============================

Text fragments from the second section of the chronicle manuscript which focuses on describing the contemporary social and political situation of Purmerend during which Louwen took on public roles in his hometown. Fragments are also classified into 'copy' or 'no-copy' depending on the inverted commas.

This section of the chronicle consists of three volumes:
Albert Pietersz. Louwen, Kronijk Der Stad Purmerende Bevattende Der Selver Opkomste En Voortgang, Manuscript, Part 2, Volume 2 (Purmerend, 1780), Noord Hollands Archief Haarlem, 143 Collectie van Louwen, A. Pietersz., inv. nr. 20. (320 pages) 
Ibid., Part 3, Volume 1 (Purmerend, 1791), Noord Hollands Archief Haarlem, 143 Collectie van Louwen, A. Pietersz., inv. nr. 21. (225 pages) 
Ibid., Part 3, Volume 2 (Purmerend, 1791), Noord Hollands Archief Haarlem, 143 Collectie van Louwen, A. Pietersz., inv. nr. 22. (168  pages) 


===============================
Historical Source Data Set (source-hist)
===============================

Samples of text from published sources explicitly mentioned by Louwen in the content of chronicle data set 1. This set is used as external data which is compared to the possible copied and paraphrased text in chronicle data set 1 to determine if the style of the chronicle fragments is similar to the sources which Louwen lists.
We selected random samples of these texts and corrected the OCR manually where needed.

Note: The selection below is not a complete list of all the books and other sources used by Louwen, but of the publications we used to create the corpus with samples

Aitzema, Lieuwe van. Saken van staet en oorlogh, in, ende omtrent de Vereenigde Nederlanden. 6 vols. ’s-Gravenhage, 1669. http://resources.huygens.knaw.nl/retroboeken/aitzema/#page=0&accessor=toc&view=homePane.
