===============================
Author Data Set (author-intros)
===============================

Samples of Louwen's writing taken from two other manuscripts by this author. This set is used as external data which is compared to the possible non-copied text in both the chronicle data sets to determine if the style of  the chronicle fragments is similar to the examples of Louwen's writing style from outside of the chronicle manuscript.

Louwen never published his work. It is unclear whether he intended some of his writings for publication. In any case the Noord-Hollands Archive in Haarlem preserves many more manuscripts by Louwen including 1: Three volumes describing the ‘Religions, Government and Armed Forces of the United provinces of the Netherland, especially of the province of Holland’; 2 ‘Political notes concerning Purmerend’ 1 volume; 3: ‘Narrative of Political and Military Histories of the Netherlands Happened in the Years 1783-1788’ 12 volumes (!) and 4: Poetry On the condition of the Netherlands in the Years 1784, 1785, 1786. (See: https://noord-hollandsarchief.nl/bronnen/archieven?mivast=236&mizig=210&miadt=236&micode=143&milang=nl&mizk_alle=louwen&miview=inv2)

The two samples are the prefaces by the author to: 

Albert Pietersz. Louwen, Beschrijvinge van de Godsdiensten, Regering En Krijgsmacht Der Vereenigde Nederlanden En de Provincie van Holland in ’t Bijsonder (1760), Noord Hollands Archief Haarlem, 143 Collectie van Louwen, A. Pietersz., inv. nr. 1-3.
And 
Albert Pietersz. Louwen, 5-17 ‘Verzaemelingen van Politieke En Militaire Vaederlandsche Geschiedenissen Voorgevallen in de Jaren 1783-1788’, (1788), Noord Hollands Archief Haarlem, 143 Collectie van Louwen, A. Pietersz., inv. nr. 5-17.

